IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: The mission of the Maryland Symphony Orchestra is to provide musical performances and programs that educate and entertain while enhancing the cultural environment of Western Maryland and the surrounding region.
IRS990.MissionDescription: The mission of the Maryland Symphony Orchestra is to provide musical performances and programs that educate and entertain while enhancing the cultural environment of Western Maryland and the surrounding region.
IRS990.Description: TO FOSTER, PROMOTE AND INCREASE THE MUSIC KNOWLEDGE OF THE PUBLIC, EXCLUSIVELY BY EDUCATIONAL ACTIVITIES, BY ORGANIZING AND PRESENTING PERFORMANCES OF MUSIC CHOSEN PRIMARILY FROM THE LITERATURE OF SYMPHONY AND CHAMBER MUSIC, OPERA SOLO RECITAL, AND VOCAL CHORUS OR DANCE.

Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.ReturnReference: Description of Uncertain Tax Positions Under FIN 48:
Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.Explanation: The Symphony adopted the provisions of the Financial Accounting Standards Codification, Accounting for Income Taxes, on January 1, 2009. This topic requires the Symphony to recognize or disclose any tax positions that would result in unrecognized tax benefits. The Symphony has no positions that would require disclosure or recognition under the topic.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section A, line 7a
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Any person, corporation, or business making a contribution of not less than ten dollars ($10.00), shall be entitled to vote at any membership meeting during the fiscal year in which the payment is made.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 11
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The 990 is reviewed by members of management before filing.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, line 19
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The organization makes its governing documents, conflict of interest policy, and financial statements available to the public upon request.
THE PROCESS HAS NOT CHANGED FROM THE PRIOR YEAR.
